Package science_fair_genetics

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Fitter
    Evaluates Nodes on their fitness using some criterion.
    Node
    Part of a tree which represents an algebraic function in the form of y=f(x).
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractFitter
    Implements adjusted fitness to reduce load implementing Fitter
    AbstractNode
    Implements a few common functions for Nodes.
    AdditionNode
    Adds its two children together.
    ConstantNode
    Returns the same constant every time it is parsed.
    DataFitter
    Determines how close a Program is to a set of data using the sum of the squared difference between returned and expected values.
    DivisionNode
    Divides one of its children by the other
    InputNode
    Returns the input when evaluated
    Main  
    MultiplicationNode
    Multiplies its children together when evaluated.
    NodeFactory
    Various factory methods for creating random Nodes and populating them.
    Population  
    Program
    A container class which holds a Node and its fitnesses as determined by a Population.
    SizeFitter
    Determines the fitness of a Node by find its size.
    SubtractionNode
    Subtracts the value of one of its children from the other when Node.evaluate(double)d.

    Enum Description
    NodeType
